description.p:
 The bit-to-cell demultiplexing by the bit-to-cell demultiplexer 1130 is defined as a mapping of the bit-interleaved input bits bdi onto the output bits be,do, where:


do is di div Nsubstreams;

div is a function that returns an integer portion of the result obtained by dividing di by Nsubstreams;

e is the demultiplexed sub-bitstream (sub-bitstream output from the bit-to-cell demultiplexer 1130) number (0 ≤ e < Nsubstreams);

vdi is the input to the bit-to-cell demultiplexer 1130;

di is the input bit number;

be,do is the output from the bit-to-cell demultiplexer 1130; and

do is the bit number of a given sub-bitstream output from the bit-to-cell demultiplexer 1130.
